<br>
While pulling, they stop, and cast FD with their back to the mobs.  Big no-no, you get bonked quite badly and it increases the chance of being interrupted.<br>
<br>
If you ever need anything answered in-game, do feel free to ask, Cirr.  I'm no whiz, but Herbie's all I've played solid for a year, and hopefully I'll have an answer for you. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->   Grats on your levels with Cirr. Well done !  Hope to group with you sometime!<br>
<br>
~edit~<br>
-Another thing when attempting to Fiegn-Split mobs that SKs can do better than Monks is the ability to snare.<br>
-Target a mob, cast Darkness. (lets say it Sticks) Mob + friends make a mad dash for you. Let them get close, FD. <br>
-Mobs stand around, and wander back in a few seconds.  <br>
-Naturally, the one with Engulfing Darkness on it is moving back slowly, and seperated from the pack.  Have someone tag (pounce) on it (much like a lion chasing the slow buffalo in the herd).<br>
<br>
Do lions hunt buffalo? I'm sleepy.  If buffalo doesn't fit, replace it with 'gazelle'.<br>
